WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:58.140 --> 00:02:03.980
Rescue on the Front
Line of Love

3
00:02:04.400 --> 00:02:08.230
If you do not wish
to remain aboard this ship...

4
00:02:08.230 --> 00:02:10.990
then you have but one destination...

5
00:02:11.780 --> 00:02:13.950
The afterlife.

6
00:02:17.740 --> 00:02:20.750
There's no way I can possibly
take this guy on...

7
00:02:21.290 --> 00:02:24.040
but I can't stay here either!

8
00:02:24.040 --> 00:02:25.500
That's the truth!

9
00:02:25.500 --> 00:02:27.000
I regret nothing!

10
00:02:27.590 --> 00:02:31.710
Well, after that little speech of yours,

11
00:02:31.710 --> 00:02:35.590
I doubt you believe you could
flee this ship unscathed...

12
00:02:36.590 --> 00:02:43.600
Or are you placing your hope in
those rats that snuck aboard?

13
00:02:57.780 --> 00:02:59.530
I wanna go back down!

14
00:03:00.120 --> 00:03:04.250
If we climb any higher,
we'll be stuck up there!

15
00:03:04.250 --> 00:03:08.000
And whichever way you look at it,
God is on board!

16
00:03:09.630 --> 00:03:10.800
That ship has sailed!

17
00:03:11.300 --> 00:03:12.630
Deal with it!

18
00:03:13.510 --> 00:03:16.510
B-But what are we gonna do, Sanji?!

19
00:03:16.510 --> 00:03:18.300
This ship is massive!

20
00:03:18.300 --> 00:03:20.600
There could be hundreds
of men on board!

21
00:03:20.600 --> 00:03:22.640
We can't possibly handle them all!

22
00:03:22.640 --> 00:03:27.100
Plus, if God or his priests
show up, we're goners!

23
00:03:27.100 --> 00:03:29.520
Ugh, will you quit whining?!

24
00:03:29.520 --> 00:03:32.110
You're always ready
with all the right tools...

25
00:03:32.110 --> 00:03:34.400
but you never wanna do anything!

26
00:03:34.400 --> 00:03:37.950
Well I wasn't ready for this!

27
00:03:40.530 --> 00:03:41.950
Anyway, listen up!

28
00:03:41.950 --> 00:03:43.750
We're dealing with mantra!

29
00:03:43.750 --> 00:03:45.870
There's no point in sneaking around!

30
00:03:46.500 --> 00:03:50.380
I'm sure they've been
on to us for a while now!

31
00:03:50.380 --> 00:03:52.000
They know?!

32
00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:53.880
What are we gonna do, then?!

33
00:03:53.880 --> 00:03:55.880
There's no point worrying about it.

34
00:03:56.470 --> 00:04:00.680
Once we're inside, we'll split up
and head straight for the deck!

35
00:04:00.680 --> 00:04:02.100
That's where Nami is!

36
00:04:02.430 --> 00:04:04.810
Wh-What?! We're gonna split up?!

37
00:04:05.480 --> 00:04:07.190
Are you insane?!

38
00:04:07.190 --> 00:04:09.650
We don't know how many
enemies are on board!

39
00:04:09.650 --> 00:04:13.690
Just getting up here was dangerous
enough! Why would we do that?!

40
00:04:13.690 --> 00:04:15.030
Dumbass!

41
00:04:16.690 --> 00:04:19.820
If we don't split up,
we'll both go down together!

42
00:04:21.070 --> 00:04:24.290
Why are you making it sound
like one of us is gonna die?

43
00:04:25.700 --> 00:04:27.910
Wait! Don't tell me you're–

44
00:04:27.910 --> 00:04:30.330
No way... For Nami...?!

45
00:04:32.130 --> 00:04:34.840
Listen, Usopp. To me...

46
00:04:35.210 --> 00:04:38.340
if it's for Nami's sake,
I'm fine with you dying.

47
00:04:38.340 --> 00:04:40.180
I'll make sure you die first!

48
00:04:40.180 --> 00:04:41.680
Alright, let's go!

49
00:04:41.680 --> 00:04:45.140
Wait for me, Nami!

50
00:04:42.970 --> 00:04:45.140
We're not done talking here!

51
00:04:45.520 --> 00:04:48.020
Nami my sweet!

52
00:04:47.060 --> 00:04:48.890
Wait, Sanji! Hold on!

53
00:04:48.890 --> 00:04:52.150
Please! Wait! Sanji!

54
00:04:57.190 --> 00:05:00.200
It seems they truly
intend to rescue you.

55
00:05:00.200 --> 00:05:03.070
How utterly ludicrous...

56
00:05:04.120 --> 00:05:05.120
Who could it be?

57
00:05:05.700 --> 00:05:09.710
Luffy is the only person still moving…

58
00:05:09.710 --> 00:05:12.250
And how did they get on board?!

59
00:05:23.470 --> 00:05:27.930
Just because they've come to save you
doesn't mean that you're saved...

60
00:05:28.600 --> 00:05:31.690
or that I'm obligated to wait for them.

61
00:05:32.600 --> 00:05:36.110
My only choice is to jump off
and hope for the best!

62
00:05:36.110 --> 00:05:38.990
If I stay here, I'll die for sure!

63
00:05:39.740 --> 00:05:41.990
I'm up against lightning...

64
00:05:41.990 --> 00:05:43.570
Is there anything I can do?!

65
00:05:56.500 --> 00:05:58.000
What's all this?

66
00:06:09.680 --> 00:06:13.440
This ship's huge,
but there's no one here!

67
00:06:13.440 --> 00:06:15.610
Does it run on its own or something?!

68
00:06:15.610 --> 00:06:18.860
And since when do
ships fly, anyway?!

69
00:06:18.860 --> 00:06:21.110
This is the first I've heard of it!

70
00:06:21.110 --> 00:06:24.910
I'm trembling just thinking
about being on this kind of ship!

71
00:06:24.910 --> 00:06:26.370
Talk about creepy!

72
00:06:26.370 --> 00:06:29.580
How the heck does
this thing even work?!

73
00:06:29.580 --> 00:06:31.290
Is it really not gonna fall?

74
00:06:32.040 --> 00:06:39.840
Plus, even if Nami is on the deck,
we're already too high up to jump off!

75
00:06:39.840 --> 00:06:42.010
What can we possibly do?!

76
00:07:03.820 --> 00:07:05.570
The sky...

77
00:07:05.570 --> 00:07:07.870
is growing darker and darker...

78
00:07:17.540 --> 00:07:18.880
Into the boats!

79
00:07:18.880 --> 00:07:20.960
Don't get left behind!

80
00:07:21.630 --> 00:07:23.380
Hurry to the White Sea!

81
00:07:23.380 --> 00:07:25.380
We're running out of time!

82
00:07:26.800 --> 00:07:28.800
What an ominous ship!

83
00:07:29.220 --> 00:07:32.810
The country really
is going to be destroyed!

84
00:07:33.600 --> 00:07:35.640
Escape from the village?!

85
00:07:35.640 --> 00:07:37.020
But, Chief!

86
00:07:37.020 --> 00:07:38.730
What about the warriors?!

87
00:07:38.730 --> 00:07:40.520
They aren't back from Upper Yard!

88
00:07:41.900 --> 00:07:44.030
There is no need to wait for them.

89
00:07:46.150 --> 00:07:47.320
You can't be serious!

90
00:07:47.320 --> 00:07:48.950
Why do you say that?

91
00:07:48.950 --> 00:07:51.450
Our warriors are not children.

92
00:07:51.450 --> 00:07:54.580
They will escape the dangers
they face on their own.

93
00:07:54.580 --> 00:07:56.210
Have faith in them.

94
00:07:57.920 --> 00:08:00.420
Enel will likely eradicate this nation.

95
00:08:00.960 --> 00:08:03.000
No doubt...

96
00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:09.720
he intends to repeat what he did
to his homeland of Birka.

97
00:08:11.640 --> 00:08:13.970
Now, hurry and set sail!

98
00:08:14.640 --> 00:08:18.100
Focus on keeping these people alive!

99
00:08:26.650 --> 00:08:28.320
It's all over.

100
00:08:28.860 --> 00:08:31.620
Wyper... it's all right now.

101
00:08:32.160 --> 00:08:34.240
You've done everything you could.

102
00:08:38.370 --> 00:08:40.670
Did you come from the Blue Sea?

103
00:08:40.670 --> 00:08:42.170
We flew up here from below.

104
00:08:42.170 --> 00:08:44.340
Do you live here?

105
00:08:46.670 --> 00:08:50.930
Everything is happening
right here in this very forest...

106
00:08:50.930 --> 00:08:53.140
yet I can't tell
what's happening inside...

107
00:08:54.760 --> 00:08:56.810
The only thing I can do is wait...

108
00:08:59.100 --> 00:09:02.980
Please be all right, everyone!

109
00:09:15.330 --> 00:09:18.250
Horsey-Bird! Horsey-Bird!

110
00:09:18.250 --> 00:09:19.330
I'm so sorry!

111
00:09:19.330 --> 00:09:21.500
You got hurt protecting me!

112
00:09:22.250 --> 00:09:24.000
Aisa!

113
00:09:24.670 --> 00:09:28.170
Aisa! Aisa!

114
00:09:28.920 --> 00:09:30.170
Luffy?

115
00:09:30.170 --> 00:09:31.380
You're alive?!

116
00:09:31.380 --> 00:09:32.720
Here!

117
00:09:32.720 --> 00:09:35.600
Over here, Aisa!

118
00:09:35.600 --> 00:09:37.680
Aisa!

119
00:09:37.680 --> 00:09:39.730
Hey! Help me!

120
00:09:40.100 --> 00:09:41.690
Here! Over here!

121
00:09:41.690 --> 00:09:43.940
How the heck did you fall like that?!

122
00:09:52.950 --> 00:09:54.120
Alright...

123
00:09:54.120 --> 00:09:57.240
Dammit, this gold ball isn't coming off!

124
00:09:57.240 --> 00:09:58.700
Hey! Phrasing!

125
00:09:58.700 --> 00:10:02.370
Anyway, let's go back
to that vine where Robin was at!

126
00:10:02.370 --> 00:10:04.630
I'm not gonna let Enel have his way!

127
00:10:04.630 --> 00:10:05.460
Okay!

128
00:10:06.460 --> 00:10:09.760
Don't think you can
stop me that easily!

129
00:10:10.130 --> 00:10:11.760
After that ship!

130
00:10:11.760 --> 00:10:13.970
I know where it's headed!

131
00:10:31.280 --> 00:10:34.570
You amuse me, girl.

132
00:10:38.780 --> 00:10:39.790
It worked!

133
00:10:39.790 --> 00:10:44.000
So such tools exist in the Blue Sea?

134
00:10:46.790 --> 00:10:49.130
Thunder Ball!

135
00:10:54.760 --> 00:10:59.930
Creating a path
for the lightning... Clever!

136
00:11:00.350 --> 00:11:04.270
Only someone well acquainted with
weather phenomena could do that.

137
00:11:05.690 --> 00:11:08.020
But... it's no use!

138
00:11:10.520 --> 00:11:17.160
Though surely you realize it won't
help you if I adjust the intensity!

139
00:11:17.160 --> 00:11:18.370
Am I wrong?

140
00:11:19.490 --> 00:11:22.040
I don't have time for this.

141
00:11:22.040 --> 00:11:22.830
Begone!

142
00:11:25.370 --> 00:11:27.630
I can't escape this time!

143
00:11:27.630 --> 00:11:28.710
You begone!

144
00:11:29.290 --> 00:11:30.920
Lethal Exploding Star!

145
00:11:42.430 --> 00:11:43.180
I...

146
00:11:43.180 --> 00:11:44.560
I'm sorry!

147
00:11:44.560 --> 00:11:45.810
Usopp!

148
00:11:45.810 --> 00:11:47.730
So it was you, huh?

149
00:11:48.310 --> 00:11:49.520
We met on that boat...

150
00:11:51.980 --> 00:11:53.940
Huh?! Where's Sanji?!

151
00:11:53.940 --> 00:11:56.200
Sanji?! He's here too?!

152
00:11:56.200 --> 00:11:58.280
You mean he hasn't arrived yet?!

153
00:12:04.500 --> 00:12:06.120
I see...

154
00:12:06.120 --> 00:12:07.410
Carry on.

155
00:12:07.410 --> 00:12:08.920
Hey, you!

156
00:12:16.170 --> 00:12:17.880
Run away…?!

157
00:12:17.880 --> 00:12:20.340
What are you running for?!
Be a man, Usopp!

158
00:12:20.930 --> 00:12:22.550
So what if you're God?!

159
00:12:30.270 --> 00:12:31.400
Usopp!

160
00:12:34.530 --> 00:12:35.320
Nami!

161
00:12:35.320 --> 00:12:36.190
What?!

162
00:12:36.190 --> 00:12:38.320
What should I do?!

163
00:12:38.320 --> 00:12:39.450
Save me!

164
00:12:39.450 --> 00:12:40.360
Screw you!

165
00:12:40.360 --> 00:12:43.870
I thought you came here to save me!

166
00:12:43.870 --> 00:12:47.200
Well, actually, I'm not really
sure what's going on...

167
00:12:47.200 --> 00:12:49.250
Then what are you doing here?!

168
00:12:49.250 --> 00:12:50.000
Who knows...?

169
00:12:50.000 --> 00:12:51.210
You don't know?!

170
00:12:51.210 --> 00:12:53.670
Save me already!

171
00:12:54.040 --> 00:12:57.420
Well, you say that...
but we're dealing with God here!

172
00:12:57.420 --> 00:12:58.470
So true!

173
00:13:07.470 --> 00:13:09.350
By the way, Nami! That hat...!

174
00:13:09.350 --> 00:13:11.100
Yeah, Luffy's hat...

175
00:13:11.100 --> 00:13:14.610
He was here earlier,
but he got thrown off!

176
00:13:14.610 --> 00:13:16.820
It's Luffy, so I'm sure he's still kicking.

177
00:13:16.820 --> 00:13:19.190
Well, the ship is ascending!

178
00:13:19.190 --> 00:13:21.280
We can't count on Luffy to help.

179
00:13:21.280 --> 00:13:21.820
Yeah!

180
00:13:21.820 --> 00:13:23.240
Let's find a way through!

181
00:13:23.240 --> 00:13:25.280
We're not dying today!

182
00:13:25.280 --> 00:13:25.990
Roger that!

183
00:13:34.080 --> 00:13:36.840
Hey! Stay by this discharge tube!

184
00:13:36.840 --> 00:13:38.840
It's gotta be important!

185
00:13:38.840 --> 00:13:40.880
I bet he won't launch
big attacks near it!

186
00:13:42.130 --> 00:13:44.550
Usopp! Look!

187
00:13:45.470 --> 00:13:46.220
A waver!

188
00:13:46.220 --> 00:13:47.970
We gotta use it to jump off!

189
00:13:48.850 --> 00:13:51.190
Jump off?! Are you crazy?!
At this height–

190
00:13:51.190 --> 00:13:55.690
Look! There are some island clouds
in the middle of the forest!

191
00:13:55.690 --> 00:13:58.190
We might survive if we make it there!

192
00:13:58.820 --> 00:14:00.190
Really?!

193
00:14:07.530 --> 00:14:08.580
Dammit!

194
00:14:10.370 --> 00:14:13.420
Ow...

195
00:14:14.750 --> 00:14:17.130
I'll find some way to distract God!

196
00:14:17.130 --> 00:14:18.000
Get it ready!

197
00:14:18.000 --> 00:14:19.000
Right!

198
00:14:20.210 --> 00:14:21.380
Take this, God!

199
00:14:22.260 --> 00:14:24.590
Usopp Spell!

200
00:14:26.430 --> 00:14:30.520
A needle is stuck deep
beneath your fingernail!

201
00:14:32.480 --> 00:14:34.600
It hurts just thinking about it!

202
00:14:34.600 --> 00:14:37.860
Do you want to die, idiot?!
Cover your ears!

203
00:14:38.570 --> 00:14:39.820
A piece of paper...

204
00:14:40.190 --> 00:14:42.650
slices across your knuckles!

205
00:14:45.530 --> 00:14:49.490
There are five canker
sores on your gums!

206
00:14:54.160 --> 00:14:55.210
Usopp!

207
00:14:58.340 --> 00:15:03.130
I gotta get ready! We'll only
have a brief moment to escape!

208
00:15:06.840 --> 00:15:07.890
Usopp!

209
00:15:15.060 --> 00:15:16.520
Looks good!

210
00:15:16.520 --> 00:15:18.480
There are island clouds by that vine!

211
00:15:18.480 --> 00:15:19.980
Alright! All set–

212
00:15:26.610 --> 00:15:28.870
Usopp!

213
00:15:32.740 --> 00:15:35.620
Try as you like to escape...

214
00:15:36.040 --> 00:15:39.130
it won't be so easy to get past me.

215
00:15:41.550 --> 00:15:47.760
Even so, are you intent on playing
a deadly game of tag with a god?

216
00:15:58.690 --> 00:16:00.310
Usopp! Grab on!

217
00:16:02.520 --> 00:16:03.730
Take my hand!

218
00:16:15.580 --> 00:16:18.670
There is no salvation
for you at this point.

219
00:16:21.460 --> 00:16:22.420
Usopp!

220
00:16:32.390 --> 00:16:33.600
Go.

221
00:16:33.600 --> 00:16:34.520
El...

222
00:16:34.520 --> 00:16:35.640
Sanji!

223
00:16:36.520 --> 00:16:37.810
Hit it, Nami!

224
00:16:40.190 --> 00:16:41.730
...Thor!

225
00:16:47.610 --> 00:16:49.200
Wait, Usopp!

226
00:16:49.200 --> 00:16:51.200
Why'd you accelerate?!
What about Sanji?!

227
00:16:51.200 --> 00:16:53.450
Never mind him! We gotta escape!

228
00:16:53.450 --> 00:16:57.450
Are you trying to stomp
all over a man's resolve?!

229
00:17:10.880 --> 00:17:12.760
So they jumped off...

230
00:17:12.760 --> 00:17:16.560
Do they still not understand
the range of my attacks?

231
00:17:16.560 --> 00:17:19.350
They haven't escaped me
in the slightest...

232
00:17:24.940 --> 00:17:26.820
Hey, God...

233
00:17:26.820 --> 00:17:29.700
There's something I wanted to say...

234
00:17:29.700 --> 00:17:32.700
But first...

235
00:17:34.320 --> 00:17:36.330
Thanks...

236
00:17:40.960 --> 00:17:45.790
I was just about to ask... for a light...

237
00:17:46.590 --> 00:17:48.380
And?

238
00:17:48.380 --> 00:17:49.550
You were about to say...?

239
00:17:50.970 --> 00:17:52.010
Oh, yeah...

240
00:17:52.550 --> 00:17:56.180
Payback's... a bitch...

241
00:18:08.360 --> 00:18:09.400
What...?

242
00:18:17.280 --> 00:18:18.330
The ship!

243
00:18:25.960 --> 00:18:27.590
You...!

244
00:18:27.590 --> 00:18:29.300
It can't be...!

245
00:18:30.300 --> 00:18:31.420
Oh, yeah...

246
00:18:32.170 --> 00:18:34.010
Payback's... a bitch...

247
00:18:34.590 --> 00:18:36.640
How dare you!

248
00:18:38.640 --> 00:18:43.100
What were you doing
inside the ship just now?!

249
00:18:46.060 --> 00:18:47.310
You mongrel!

250
00:18:47.860 --> 00:18:49.320
Such insolence!

251
00:18:50.480 --> 00:18:53.150
The gears have gone awry...

252
00:18:53.150 --> 00:18:54.320
I must fix them!

253
00:19:17.090 --> 00:19:19.100
Don't worry!

254
00:19:19.100 --> 00:19:21.390
Nami safely fell
onto some island clouds!

255
00:19:27.480 --> 00:19:28.980
Usopp...

256
00:19:29.770 --> 00:19:30.980
Hopping!

257
00:19:34.490 --> 00:19:36.660
Nooo!

258
00:19:36.660 --> 00:19:38.780
I'm falling! I'm gonna crash!

259
00:19:38.780 --> 00:19:41.700
I'm gonna c-crash and die!

260
00:19:55.800 --> 00:19:57.760
Usopp! Sanji!

261
00:19:58.340 --> 00:19:59.930
Is that you, Nami?!

262
00:19:59.930 --> 00:20:01.560
Sounds like you made it!

263
00:20:01.560 --> 00:20:02.890
What a relief!

264
00:20:03.770 --> 00:20:05.430
Wow, Sanji!

265
00:20:04.060 --> 00:20:05.810
Are you okay, Sanji?!

266
00:20:05.430 --> 00:20:07.560
You were really manly!

267
00:20:05.810 --> 00:20:10.650
I'm so sorry you had to get
all charred again just for us!

268
00:20:07.560 --> 00:20:09.560
Don't go dying on us!

269
00:20:09.560 --> 00:20:10.650
You hear me?

270
00:20:11.230 --> 00:20:14.610
I c-can't... I c-can't breathe! N-Nami!

271
00:20:14.610 --> 00:20:16.780
Hurry! Pull me outta here, quick!

272
00:20:16.780 --> 00:20:17.700
Oh. Sorry.

273
00:20:18.360 --> 00:20:21.870
Anyway, let's get out of here...

274
00:20:21.870 --> 00:20:22.620
I'm gonna die...

275
00:20:36.340 --> 00:20:39.050
Curse you, Blue Sea dweller!

276
00:20:43.390 --> 00:20:46.980
This ship will not be
brought down so easily.

277
00:20:48.350 --> 00:20:52.940
I'm fully acquainted
with the ship's power circuits.

278
00:20:52.940 --> 00:20:58.700
Even without electricity,
the two hundred jet dials I gathered

279
00:20:58.700 --> 00:21:02.030
from my homeland of Birka...

280
00:21:03.910 --> 00:21:07.910
will keep this ship afloat
for a while with wind power.

281
00:21:08.660 --> 00:21:12.000
No matter what
you feeble beings try...

282
00:21:22.720 --> 00:21:27.140
this country's fate will not change!

283
00:21:30.140 --> 00:21:33.060
Look! That huge vine!

284
00:21:33.060 --> 00:21:35.690
If it's the same one I saw in the ruins,

285
00:21:35.690 --> 00:21:39.190
these are the island
clouds above them.

286
00:21:39.190 --> 00:21:42.280
Ruins...? Wait, the City
of Gold?! It exists?!

287
00:21:42.780 --> 00:21:43.780
Yeah.

288
00:21:43.780 --> 00:21:47.370
But Enel already swiped all the gold.

289
00:21:47.370 --> 00:21:51.580
In any case, the others
should be in the ruins below!

290
00:21:47.740 --> 00:21:51.580
Ruins of Shandora

291
00:21:49.870 --> 00:21:50.370
Current Location

292
00:21:50.620 --> 00:21:51.080
Current Location

293
00:21:51.370 --> 00:21:51.580
Current Location

294
00:21:52.080 --> 00:21:55.000
I'm not familiar with
the topography like you are...

295
00:21:56.670 --> 00:22:00.840
but... I do know that
it's dangerous to stay here!

296
00:22:00.840 --> 00:22:02.630
Yeah. Get on!

297
00:22:02.630 --> 00:22:04.850
Let's find everyone
and get off this island!

298
00:22:05.470 --> 00:22:06.300
Y-Yeah!

299
00:22:08.140 --> 00:22:12.310
There isn't a single
safe place left in Skypiea...

300
00:22:29.660 --> 00:22:31.710
Luffy, look out!

301
00:22:40.340 --> 00:22:41.380
So fast!

302
00:22:41.380 --> 00:22:43.130
L-L-Luffy!

303
00:22:43.130 --> 00:22:45.090
Wait! Not that way!

304
00:22:45.090 --> 00:22:47.600
Left! Left!

305
00:22:47.600 --> 00:22:50.470
H-H-Huh?! I can't t-turn that fast!

306
00:22:51.220 --> 00:22:54.690
Gum-Gum Hook!

307
00:23:02.030 --> 00:23:04.820
Don't destroy my homeland!

308
00:23:05.610 --> 00:23:08.070
You can see Giant Jack right there!

309
00:23:08.070 --> 00:23:09.330
I know, but–

310
00:23:10.410 --> 00:23:11.830
Quit destroying stuff!

311
00:23:13.200 --> 00:23:14.830
Stop!

312
00:23:17.790 --> 00:23:19.040
Huh?!

313
00:23:20.960 --> 00:23:23.720
Where did everyone go?!
Robin, Zoro, Chopper...

314
00:23:23.720 --> 00:23:25.970
Wyper and God too...

315
00:23:26.550 --> 00:23:29.300
They must've already climbed up.

316
00:23:29.300 --> 00:23:31.560
Of course! Robin!

317
00:23:31.560 --> 00:23:33.270
Alright! Let's go!

318
00:23:35.520 --> 00:23:37.190
Huh? Aisa?

319
00:23:41.230 --> 00:23:42.230
Luffy...

320
00:23:42.230 --> 00:23:43.900
Is the sky island...

321
00:23:45.240 --> 00:23:47.160
going to disappear?!

322
00:24:07.760 --> 00:24:10.470
Wyper and the others
are right through here!

323
00:24:17.980 --> 00:24:20.860
The ship is still headed
toward the grand bell!

324
00:24:21.610 --> 00:24:24.230
What happened to
the navigator and the others?

325
00:24:24.230 --> 00:24:27.320
If they're on board,
could that mean they're...?

326
00:24:31.530 --> 00:24:34.370
We made it through!

327
00:24:38.040 --> 00:24:41.040
Down there! Luffy! Stop! Stop!

328
00:24:41.420 --> 00:24:42.380
Robin!

329
00:24:42.380 --> 00:24:43.420
Huh?

330
00:24:43.420 --> 00:24:45.210
Wh-What're you doing?!

331
00:24:45.210 --> 00:24:46.840
Look after these guys!

332
00:24:58.520 --> 00:24:59.810
Stop! Stop!

333
00:25:02.230 --> 00:25:03.520
Luffy...

334
00:25:04.730 --> 00:25:06.190
Y-You grew hands!

335
00:25:07.070 --> 00:25:09.400
What's with that gold on your arm?!

336
00:25:09.400 --> 00:25:13.700
Robin! The golden bell
is at the top of this vine, right?!

337
00:25:13.700 --> 00:25:16.870
And Enel's after it, right?!

338
00:25:16.870 --> 00:25:21.960
Well, if the bell does exist,
it would have to be there...

339
00:25:21.960 --> 00:25:22.830
But he's already...

340
00:25:22.830 --> 00:25:23.880
Alright, then!

341
00:25:26.460 --> 00:25:27.420
Luffy!

342
00:25:28.630 --> 00:25:29.880
Excuse me...

343
00:25:30.880 --> 00:25:32.640
Where is our navigator?

344
00:25:32.640 --> 00:25:34.010
She has orange hair...

345
00:25:34.010 --> 00:25:35.850
What? Nami? She's on that ship...

346
00:25:38.310 --> 00:25:42.270
Huh? But I only hear one voice
coming from the sky now...

347
00:25:47.400 --> 00:25:48.610
There they are!

348
00:25:52.740 --> 00:25:54.280
Robin!

349
00:25:54.780 --> 00:25:58.080
Miss Navigator! Long Nose! Mr. Cook!

350
00:25:59.700 --> 00:26:01.000
Aisa!

351
00:26:01.790 --> 00:26:03.830
Thank goodness! Are you all right?!

352
00:26:03.830 --> 00:26:05.590
Nami!

353
00:26:07.170 --> 00:26:08.920
Zoro! Chopper!

354
00:26:08.920 --> 00:26:10.550
Weird old man!

355
00:26:10.550 --> 00:26:12.630
A g-guerilla...

356
00:26:12.630 --> 00:26:13.930
Dammit!

357
00:26:13.930 --> 00:26:15.760
Everyone's been taken out!

358
00:26:15.760 --> 00:26:18.100
Oh, if only I'd been there!

359
00:26:18.100 --> 00:26:21.350
Right, Aisa! Where's Luffy?!
Wasn't he with you?!

360
00:26:21.350 --> 00:26:27.900
Luffy just went up the vine
to rescue you from Enel!

361
00:26:27.900 --> 00:26:28.980
Huh?!

362
00:26:28.980 --> 00:26:30.820
You mean we just
missed each other?!

363
00:26:31.190 --> 00:26:33.990
He left just now.
I tried to stop him, but...

364
00:26:34.660 --> 00:26:36.280
Talk about bad timing!

365
00:26:36.280 --> 00:26:38.620
Speaking of time,
we don't have much left!

366
00:26:38.620 --> 00:26:39.990
We gotta escape now!

367
00:26:40.870 --> 00:26:42.080
Go ahead!

368
00:26:42.080 --> 00:26:43.580
I'll go after him on the waver!

369
00:26:44.460 --> 00:26:46.750
You guys just find
a way to the Merry!

370
00:26:46.750 --> 00:26:47.540
What?!

371
00:26:52.470 --> 00:26:53.470
Dammit!

372
00:26:53.470 --> 00:26:55.590
That ship's fast!

373
00:26:55.970 --> 00:27:00.600
Enel!

374
00:27:00.640 --> 00:27:06.400
Shandian Village
Hidden in the Clouds

375
00:27:02.270 --> 00:27:03.690
Get on, quickly!

376
00:27:03.690 --> 00:27:05.600
The sky's getting darker!

377
00:27:12.320 --> 00:27:13.490
What's wrong?

378
00:27:13.490 --> 00:27:15.240
You need to escape at once...

379
00:27:15.240 --> 00:27:17.870
Chief... A-Aisa still hasn't–

380
00:27:17.870 --> 00:27:19.950
I see. She hasn't returned...

381
00:27:20.370 --> 00:27:22.700
Aisa is a bright child.

382
00:27:22.700 --> 00:27:26.500
Let us have faith she's
with one of the warriors...

383
00:27:32.340 --> 00:27:35.630
Looks like the thunderclouds
are pouring out smoothly.

384
00:27:38.220 --> 00:27:43.850
Angel Island
Skypiea

385
00:27:44.310 --> 00:27:46.520
Come on! Hurry up!

386
00:27:46.520 --> 00:27:47.310
Captain!

387
00:27:47.770 --> 00:27:51.070
We need to use
the boats at the port too!

388
00:27:51.440 --> 00:27:53.570
They'd have to go around
the long way!

389
00:27:53.570 --> 00:27:56.950
Men! Use dials to create rivers
across the island at once!

390
00:27:56.950 --> 00:27:57.780
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

391
00:27:58.200 --> 00:28:00.700
How many citizens are left?!

392
00:28:00.700 --> 00:28:02.240
Still at least half of them...!

393
00:28:02.740 --> 00:28:04.910
Tell them to leave their belongings!

394
00:28:04.910 --> 00:28:07.750
Just get all the citizens out to sea!

395
00:28:07.750 --> 00:28:08.920
Yes, sir!

396
00:28:17.590 --> 00:28:18.590
Hold it!

397
00:28:18.590 --> 00:28:23.310
Leave the departure fee!
Two billion extol per person!

398
00:28:23.310 --> 00:28:26.430
Miss Amazon!
You need to escape, too!

399
00:28:26.430 --> 00:28:27.020
Huh?

400
00:28:27.020 --> 00:28:29.270
Hurry! To Cloud End!

401
00:28:27.060 --> 00:28:31.980
Heaven's Gate
White Sea

402
00:28:29.270 --> 00:28:29.730
Huh?

403
00:28:29.730 --> 00:28:31.440
This country...

404
00:28:31.440 --> 00:28:31.980
Huh?

405
00:28:31.980 --> 00:28:35.740
It's about to be destroyed!

406
00:28:36.900 --> 00:28:38.280
Huh?

407
00:28:55.050 --> 00:28:56.760
The wind stopped...

408
00:29:19.070 --> 00:29:21.240
Run! Run!

409
00:29:31.460 --> 00:29:34.090
The time has come.

410
00:29:34.090 --> 00:29:36.590
Now then. Let us...

411
00:29:39.090 --> 00:29:41.470
begin the festivities.

412
00:29:48.930 --> 00:29:50.640
Mamaragan!

413
00:30:00.450 --> 00:30:03.360
Angel Island
White-White Sea

414
00:30:00.860 --> 00:30:02.660
Get away from the island!

415
00:30:02.660 --> 00:30:04.620
Don't dawdle!

416
00:30:05.950 --> 00:30:08.410
The lightning keeps getting bigger!

417
00:30:08.410 --> 00:30:10.460
The boats in the port are wrecked!

418
00:30:10.460 --> 00:30:13.290
To the western end
of the beach! Quickly!

419
00:30:13.290 --> 00:30:14.750
There are still boats there!

420
00:30:14.750 --> 00:30:16.130
Run to the west!

421
00:30:16.670 --> 00:30:19.590
Quickly! Just drop your belongings!

422
00:30:28.720 --> 00:30:31.230
Chief! You need to get on a boat!

423
00:30:31.810 --> 00:30:32.940
Yes...

424
00:30:33.600 --> 00:30:36.400
Great Warrior Kalgara...

425
00:30:37.270 --> 00:30:40.110
please protect everyone...

426
00:30:56.500 --> 00:30:58.710
This lightning is massive!

427
00:30:59.090 --> 00:31:02.170
We're gonna end up as
sky dust if we stay here!

428
00:31:04.970 --> 00:31:06.970
Everyone! Hurry to the ship!

429
00:31:06.970 --> 00:31:09.470
I'll meet up with you
as soon as I get Luffy!

430
00:31:09.470 --> 00:31:11.350
A-A-Alright! Got it!

431
00:31:17.560 --> 00:31:18.770
Hurry, Robin!

432
00:31:19.400 --> 00:31:22.030
We gotta carry these guys
to the ship somehow!

433
00:31:22.030 --> 00:31:23.240
Wyper!

434
00:31:31.620 --> 00:31:32.790
Swordsman!

435
00:31:34.370 --> 00:31:35.460
Weird old man!

436
00:31:35.790 --> 00:31:37.790
Thank goodness! You're conscious!

437
00:31:37.790 --> 00:31:40.340
Hey! There's no time!
Can you walk?!

438
00:31:40.800 --> 00:31:44.300
Enel! So you've begun...

439
00:31:50.350 --> 00:31:52.010
Let's hurry.

440
00:31:52.010 --> 00:31:54.600
There's nothing we can do
even if we stay here.

441
00:31:58.560 --> 00:32:00.060
Wyper...

442
00:32:04.360 --> 00:32:07.860
Not even Luffy can deal with
an enemy ascending into the sky!

443
00:32:07.860 --> 00:32:11.990
I have to make it in time! We need to
escape before this country's destroyed!

444
00:32:22.170 --> 00:32:23.670
What an exquisite view!

445
00:32:26.220 --> 00:32:30.970
Don't assume things are gonna
turn out how you want, Enel!
